In majority voting the class label (y) is predicted as, Y = mode {$P_{1}$, $P_{2}$, …, $P_{n}$} where $P_{1}$, $P_{2}$, …, $P_{n}$ are the predictions of n classifiers that are combined. Here $P_{1}$ = 0, $P_{2}$ = 0, …, $P_{3}$ = 1. And Y can be calculated as,

Y = mode {$P_{1}$, $P_{2}$, $P_{3}$}

= mode {0, 0, 1}

= 0
